   Your Link to Public Safety Resources for the Town of Fountain Hills
   Town of Fountain Hills / Public Safety
   [pixel.gif]



   [glassbullet.gif] Fountain Hills Marshals Department

        The Fountain Hills Marshals Department, led by Public Safety
   Director Steven Gendler, is the town's municipal law enforcement
   agency.

   [BrushStroke.gif]
   [glassbullet.gif] Fountain Hills Magistrate Court

        The Town Magistrate's Court is presided over by Judge Stuart J.
   Shoob.

   [BrushStroke.gif]
   [glassbullet.gif] Maricopa County Sheriffs Office

       The Maricopa County Sheriff's Office, under contract with the Town
   of Fountain Hills, enforces state laws, deters criminal activity,
   protects life and property, and maintains order.

   [BrushStroke.gif]
   [glassbullet.gif] Arizona Department of Public Safety

       The Arizona Department of Public Safety is a statewide law
   enforcement agency committed to providing  professional quality police
   and support services to the public and to the criminal justice
   community.

   [BrushStroke.gif]
   [glassbullet.gif] Rural/Metro Corporation

       Rural/Metro Corporation is a provider of mobile healthcare
   services, including emergency and non-emergency ambulance
   transportation, fire protection and other safety-related services to
   our community.

   [pixel.gif]

